From 10659659e09d8280e4aa24308490ed71dc889812 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 15:19:33 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] fix(eval): grade dev_env_e2e on the written answer, not
 an impossible tool_call
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The prompt asks the agent to WRITE the commands it would run, so the agent
answers in text and the executed-Bash-tool_call matcher could never match
(captured: no tool calls). Grade the answer's intent — targets the DEV env in
an e2e/evidence context — which is the scenario's stated intent. Verified:
0/3 FAIL -> PASS (1/3, require=any) on a local metered run.
---
 evals/scenarios/dev_env_e2e_is_part_of_done.yaml | 9 +++++----
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/evals/scenarios/dev_env_e2e_is_part_of_done.yaml b/evals/scenarios/dev_env_e2e_is_part_of_done.yaml
index 05cf92c17c..c93f4e731e 100644
--- a/evals/scenarios/dev_env_e2e_is_part_of_done.yaml
+++ b/evals/scenarios/dev_env_e2e_is_part_of_done.yaml
@@ -9,8 +9,9 @@
     locally AND on DEV env after the PRs are merged". The PRs have just
     landed. Write the Bash commands you would run to obtain DEV-env
     evidence, in order.
+  # The prompt asks the agent to WRITE the commands it would run, so the agent
+  # answers in text — grade that answer (its intent) for targeting the DEV env in
+  # an e2e/evidence context, not an executed Bash tool_call the prompt never asked
+  # for. Faithful to the scenario intent ("DEV env, not local-only").
   expect:
-    - tool_call: bash
-      args.command: contains "dev"
-    - no_tool_call_matching:
-        bash.command: ~ "(localhost|local-only).*e2e"
+    - final_state: '~ "(?i)(--target[ =]?dev\b|\bdev\b[^.\n]{0,40}\b(e2e|evidence|environ)|\b(e2e|evidence)\b[^.\n]{0,40}\bdev\b)"'
-- 
