The clean-room runner ran scenarios in an empty temp dir, so a prompt that
presupposes a working tree ('changes are staged', 'squash the commits') sent the
agent investigating the empty-cwd mismatch instead of firing the canonical
command — a false negative; the skill was correct all along. Add an opt-in
fixture: git_repo (staged change, commits to squash, an origin remote) wired
through the EvalSpec/loader/runner so the sandbox state matches the prompt. The
five ship-delivery probes are extracted to ship_scenario.py (keeping the over-cap
per_skill.py shrinking) and now pass.
