 probes; grade arg-less tool calls
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Two honest grading corrections, both making CORRECT agent behaviour pass:

- Centralise git_repo fixture assignment in all_scenarios.py and extend it to
  repo-dependent probes (main_clone hotfix, regression-test-before-push, merge
  reconcile, ...) plus the hand-authored yaml that presuppose a working tree.
- matchers.py: a positive tool-call matcher now treats an ABSENT arg as '' so a
  tool-presence matcher (~ ".*") passes when the agent calls the tool with no
  arg — e.g. a correct TaskList() reading the whole live list. Value-pinning
  regexes still fail against '', so they are unchanged; negative matchers are
  untouched. Fixes todos_built_dynamically.
